Additionally, a dish consisting of grilled {{ill|Unagi|ja|鰻|12=draft}} wrapped around a bamboo skewer is sometimes named "Kurikara-yaki" (くりから焼き) after the sword, due to its resemblance in shape.<ref>{{Google books|yqrUDgAAQBAJ|美味い話にゃ肴あり 8巻|page=39}}, accessed November 13, 2021.</ref><ref>{{Google books|OaNBDwAAQBAJ|古地図片手に記者が行く 「鬼平犯科帳」から見える東京21世紀|page=244}}, accessed November 13, 2021.</ref>
== In Fiction == * In the Japanese manga {{ill|Blue Exorcist|ja|青の祓魔師|12=draft}}, a weapon called the Kurikara<ref>[https://aonoexorcist.fandom.com/wiki/Kurikara Kurikara | Ao no Exorcist Wiki | Fandom]</ref> appears. It is the principal image ({{ill|honzon|ja|本尊|12=draft}}) of a fictional religion known as {{ill|Myōō Dharani|ja|明王陀羅尼宗|12=draft}}, which venerates {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|12=draft}}. According to the narrative, it once housed the spirit of {{ill|Karura|ja|迦楼羅天|lt=Karura|lt_ja=迦褸羅|12=draft}} and vanquished the unclean king.
