{{redirect|Kurikara Fudō|Temples Known as "Kurikara Fudō"|{{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利迦羅不動寺|qq=draft}}}}
{{出典の明記|date=October 4, 2015 (Sun) 11:51 (UTC)}} [[File:Sword Dragon Kurikara (Nara National Museum).jpg|thumb|150px|Kurikara Dragon Sword with Two Child Deity Images, housed at the {{ill|Nara National Museum|ja|奈良国立博物館|qq=draft}}, Important Cultural Property]] [[File:Kurikara Dragon Sutra Box.JPG|thumb|150px|Kurikara Dragon Maki-e Sutra Box, housed in the Okuninushi-in of [[Taimadera]] in Nara, National Treasure]] [[File: Kurikara Doragon.jpg|150px|thumb|A framed depiction of the {{ill|Kurikara Dragon King|ja|倶利伽羅竜王|qq=draft}}]] '''Kurikara Sword''', (倶利伽羅剣) is the sword held in the right hand by the standing image of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft}}.<ref name="bank">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E5%80%B6%E5%88%A9%E4%BC%BD%E7%BE%85%E5%89%A3-1716677 |title=倶利伽羅剣(くりからけん) |publisher=Kotobank |accessdate=2017-01-17}}</ref> In the {{ill|Samaya form|ja|三昧耶形|1=Samaya Symbols|lt=Samaya form|qq=draft}}, it serves as the very symbol of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft}} and is regarded as the "Sword of Wisdom" that shatters the three poisons (greed, anger, and ignorance). The sword derives its name from the depiction of the {{ill|Kurikara Dragon King|ja|倶利伽羅竜王|qq=draft}} entwined by raging {{ill|flames|ja|炎|qq=draft}} around it.<ref name="bank" />
The {{ill|Atsuta Shrine|ja|熱田神宮|qq=draft}} in [[Nagoya, Aichi Prefecture]] houses a sword of the same name, which is recorded as a sacred treasure of the subsidiary shrine {{ill|Hakkengū|ja|別宮八剣宮|qq=draft}} in the "Chōshū Zasshi".<ref name="愛知">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.pref.aichi.jp/kyoiku/bunka/bunkazainavi/yukei/kougei/kensitei/0572.html |title=倶利迦羅剣（くりからけん） |publisher=Aichi Prefecture |accessdate=2017-01-17}}</ref> In [[1971]] (Showa 46), it was designated as a Cultural Property by Aichi Prefecture.<ref name="愛知" />
Additionally, a dish consisting of grilled {{ill|Unagi|ja|鰻|qq=draft}} wrapped around a bamboo skewer is sometimes named "Kurikara-yaki" (くりから焼き) after the sword, due to its resemblance in shape.<ref>{{Google books|yqrUDgAAQBAJ|美味い話にゃ肴あり 8巻|page=39}}, accessed November 13, 2021.</ref><ref>{{Google books|OaNBDwAAQBAJ|古地図片手に記者が行く 「鬼平犯科帳」から見える東京21世紀|page=244}}, accessed November 13, 2021.</ref>
== In Fiction == * In the Japanese manga {{ill|Blue Exorcist|ja|青の祓魔師|qq=draft}}, a weapon called the Kurikara<ref>[https://aonoexorcist.fandom.com/wiki/Kurikara Kurikara | Ao no Exorcist Wiki | Fandom]</ref> appears. It is the principal image ({{ill|honzon|ja|本尊|qq=draft}}) of a fictional religion known as {{ill|Myōō Dharani|ja|明王陀羅尼宗|qq=draft}}, which venerates {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft}}. According to the narrative, it once housed the spirit of {{ill|Karura|ja|迦楼羅天|lt=Karura|lt_ja=迦褸羅|qq=draft}} and vanquished the unclean king.
