== In Fiction == * In the Japanese manga {{ill|Blue Exorcist|ja|青の祓魔師|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Blue Exorcist|qq=}}, a weapon called the Kurikara<ref>[https://aonoexorcist.fandom.com/wiki/Kurikara Kurikara | Ao no Exorcist Wiki | Fandom]</ref> appears. It is the principal image ({{ill|honzon|ja|本尊|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/honzon|qq=}}) of a fictional religion known as {{ill|Myōō Dharani|ja|明王陀羅尼宗|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōō Dharani|qq=}}, which venerates {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Myōō|lt=Fudō Myōō|1=Acala|2=ja|3=不動明王|13=User:Immanuelle/Acala|qq=}}. According to the narrative, it once housed the spirit of {{ill|Karura|ja|迦楼羅天|lt=Karura|lt_ja=迦褸羅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karura|qq=}} and vanquished the unclean king.
