{{出典の明記|date=October 4, 2015 (Sun) 11:51 (UTC)}} [[File:Sword Dragon Kurikara (Nara National Museum).jpg|thumb|150px|Kurikara Dragon Sword with Two Child Deity Images, housed at the {{ill|Nara National Museum|ja|奈良国立博物館|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara National Museum|qq=}}, Important Cultural Property]] [[File:Kurikara Dragon Sutra Box.JPG|thumb|150px|Kurikara Dragon Maki-e Sutra Box, housed in the Okuninushi-in of [[Taimadera]] in Nara, National Treasure]] [[File: Kurikara Doragon.jpg|150px|thumb|A framed depiction of the {{ill|Kurikara Dragon King|ja|倶利伽羅竜王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Dragon King|qq=}}]] '''Kurikara Sword''', (倶利伽羅剣) is the sword held in the right hand by the standing image of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Myōō|lt=Fudō Myōō|1=Acala|2=ja|3=不動明王|13=User:Immanuelle/Acala|qq=}}.<ref name="bank">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E5%80%B6%E5%88%A9%E4%BC%BD%E7%BE%85%E5%89%A3-1716677 |title=倶利伽羅剣(くりからけん) |publisher=Kotobank |accessdate=2017-01-17}}</ref> In the {{ill|Samaya form|ja|三昧耶形|1=Samaya Symbols|lt=Samaya form|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Samaya form|13=User:Immanuelle/Samaya Symbols|qq=}}, it serves as the very symbol of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Myōō|lt=Fudō Myōō|1=Acala|2=ja|3=不動明王|13=User:Immanuelle/Acala|qq=}} and is regarded as the "Sword of Wisdom" that shatters the three poisons (greed, anger, and ignorance). The sword derives its name from the depiction of the {{ill|Kurikara Dragon King|ja|倶利伽羅竜王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Dragon King|qq=}} entwined by raging {{ill|flames|ja|炎|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/flames|qq=}} around it.<ref name="bank" />
